               <p>2026. <persName id="def1-2026-18480821" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-2026-18480821" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2026-18480821" type="age" value="37"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2026-18480821" type="surname" value="LEARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2026-18480821" type="given" value="ARTHUR"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">ARTHUR LEARY</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-2026-18480821" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-2026-18480821" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2026-18480821" type="age" value="44"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2026-18480821" type="surname" value="COOPER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2026-18480821" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">RICHARD COOPER</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18480821-2026-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18480821-2026-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18480821-2026-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp>, unlawfully utter<lb></lb>ing counterfeit coin.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. BODKIN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">DAWSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-1421" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1421" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1421" type="surname" value="PERRIAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1421" type="given" value="ELIZA"></interp>ELIZA PERRIAN</persName>
                  </hi>. My husband keeps the Joiner's Arms, beer-shop, at Lewisham. On 20th July, about twelve o'clock in the day, the prisoner Cooper came and asked for half a pint of porter—it came to a penny—he gave me a bad half-crown—I looked at it, threw it down, and told him it was bad—he snatched it up instantly, and gave me a good one—he went out and I sent a boy to follow him—I saw Cooper join Leary and another—they went to Lee.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How far were the other persons from you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About 100 yards—I had never seen Cooper before—he was at our place about two minutes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-1422" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1422" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1422" type="surname" value="BOOKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1422" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH BOOKER</persName>
                  </hi>. My husband keeps the Highlander, at Lee, about a mile from the Joiner's Arms. On 26th July, Leary came there about half-past twelve o'clock, and asked for a pint of beer which came to twopence—he gave me a bad half-crown—I gave him the change—he left—I thought it was not good, and laid it on a shelf—there was no other money there—my brother was standing at the door—I called his attention to the half-crown, about ten minutes after Leary was gone—he took it and went after Leary.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Where do you generally put money? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> In the</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184808210204"></xptr>
               <p>till—I suspected at first it was bad—I am sure I got it from Leary—no customer came in from the time I placed it on the shelf, till I asked my brother about it—I did not throw it in a place where there was other money—there is a bowl kept in the till, which is a drawer in the bottom shelf of the cupboard—when I receive money I go to the cupboard—I laid the half-crown on the third shelf, distinct from the till.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-1423" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1423" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1423" type="surname" value="BOOKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1423" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BOOKER</persName>
                  </hi>. On 26th July my sister gave me this half-crown—I saw it was bad—I went in pursuit of Leary—I saw him and Cooper, about ten rods off on the right, on the road to Lee—I followed and cave them in charge at the Tigier's Head—on going along the road they fell in conver<lb></lb>sation with another man—I gave the half-crown my sister gave me, to the sergeant.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-1424" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1424" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1424" type="surname" value="JENKINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1424" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES JENKINS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant, R</hi> 10). Booker came to me—I went to the Tiger's Head, and saw the prisoners in conversation—the other man had left hem—Leary was about to enter the Tiger's Head—I took him and Cooper to the station—I found this half-crown in Leary's hand—I was about to search Cooper—he took his right hand from his pocket, and in it was this half-crown—I bent the two half-crowns between my teeth, and found they were bad—I found a penny on each of the prisoners—this is the half-crown I received from Booker.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-1425" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1425" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1425" type="surname" value="POWELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1425" type="given" value="CALEB EDWARD"></interp>CALEB EDWARD POWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of coin to the Royal Mint. These three half-crowns are all counterfeit, and have all been cast in the same mould.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">LEARY</hi>—<hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18480821-2026-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
